All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
Car
The Car class represents a car object with various properties.
CarCsvReader
The CarCsvReader class reads created car data from a CSV file.
CarCsvWriter
The CarCsvWriter class writes Car data to a CSV file.
Card
The Card class represents a playing card with a specific value and suit.
CarFactory
The CarFactory class creates random Car objects.
HandEvaluator
The HandEvaluator class represents a utility for evaluating poker hands and calculating their probabilities.
MontyHall
The MontyHall class is a simulation of the Monty Hall problem.
Person
The Person class represents individuals with birthdays and provides methods related to the birthday problem.
SetOperations
This class provides methods for performing set operations on lists of strings.
StatsLibrary
This class provides a collection of statistical and probability functions.
TestHandEvaluator
A test class for evaluating and testing the functionality of the HandEvaluator class.
TestMontyHall
The TestMontyHall class runs simulations of the Monty Hall problem.
TestPerson
A test class for evaluating and testing the functionality of the Person class to solve the birthday problem.
TestSetOperations
This class is used for testing the SetOperations class, which provides functions to perform set operations on ArrayLists.
TestStatsLibrary
This class is used for testing the functionality of the StatsLibrary class, which provides various functions for probability and statistics.
